You may strip Germany of her colonies, reduce her armaments ... and
her navy. ... All the same, in the end, if she feels that she has been
unjustly treated. . , she will find means of exacting retribution. ... The
maintenance of peace ... will depend upon there being no cause of
exasperation constantly stirring up the spirit of patriotism, of justice,
or of fair play to achieve redress.
